    {
        "content": "<p>after further thought, a new question occurs to me:</p>\n<p>Do all definitions have <code>Prop</code> before the <code>:=</code> ?</p>\n<p>The the few that I've looked up do.</p>",
        "id": 484084745,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1732385741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No.  Look back at the example in Eric Wieser's first answer in this thread:<br>\n<code>def double (a : ℕ) : ℕ := 2 * a</code></p>",
        "id": 484085322,
        "sender_full_name": "Dan Velleman",
        "timestamp": 1732386256
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>thanks - silly me ! :)</p>",
        "id": 484085364,
        "sender_full_name": "rzeta0",
        "timestamp": 1732386284
